body:
This seems to be a longstanding issue, unrelated to recent fixes in completion code:
```console
$ bin/podman __completeNoDesc ps --format '{{.Created.' 
{{.Created.wall}}
{{.Created.ext}}
{{.Created.loc.
{{.Created.Add}}
{{.Created.AddDate}}
{{.Created.After}}
{{.Created.AppendFormat}}
{{.Created.Before}}
{{.Created.Clock}}
{{.Created.Date}}
{{.Created.Day}}
{{.Created.Equal}}
{{.Created.Format}}
{{.Created.GobEncode}}
{{.Created.Hour}}
{{.Created.ISOWeek}}
{{.Created.In}}
{{.Created.IsZero}}
{{.Created.Local}}
{{.Created.Location}}
{{.Created.MarshalBinary}}
{{.Created.MarshalJSON}}
{{.Created.MarshalText}}
{{.Created.Minute}}
{{.Created.Month}}
{{.Created.Nanosecond}}
{{.Created.Round}}
{{.Created.Second}}
{{.Created.String}}
{{.Created.Sub}}
{{.Created.Truncate}}
{{.Created.UTC}}
{{.Created.Unix}}
{{.Created.UnixNano}}
{{.Created.Weekday}}
{{.Created.Year}}
{{.Created.YearDay}}
{{.Created.Zone}}
```
(same with `secret ls/inspect`, `volume ls/inspect`, `image`, `events`, and others)

In `ps`, some of those actually work, and others fail with reasonable messages:
```console
$ bin/podman ps --format '{{.Created.UTC}}'
2022-05-11 16:33:53.341353432 +0000 UTC
$ bin/podman ps --format '{{.Created.Minute}}'
33
$ bin/podman ps --format '{{.Created.Zone}}'
Error: template: ps:1:21: executing "ps" at <.Created.Zone>: can't call method/function "Zone" with 2 results
$ bin/podman ps --format '{{.Created.wall}}'
Error: template: ps:1:21: executing "ps" at <.Created.wall>: wall is an unexported field of struct type time.Time
$ bin/podman ps --format '{{.Created.Truncate}}'
Error: template: ps:1:21: executing "ps" at <.Created.Truncate>: wrong number of args for Truncate: want 1 got 0
```
I don't know if it's possible to (programmatically) exclude the nonworking fields. If it's possible, it would make things user-friendlier.

In other podman subcommands, none of the subfields are usable at all:
```console
$ bin/podman secret ls --format '{{.UpdatedAt.Year}}'  (or whatever)
Error: template: list:1:23: executing "list" at <.UpdatedAt.Year>: can't evaluate field Year in type string
```
My uneducated guess is that these could (and should?) easily be fixed to handle date fields more like `ps` by just making a library call or two. But I'm just guessing.
